other: This card was difficult to transcribe in parts, due to the style of the index card. In the top left corner is written "c. TL 3328" and "1340", although I was unsure if this relates to the grid reference. In the top centre of the card is written "Circumstances, said to have been found 10 to 15 years ago, by Mr Fiddler; found on bank of the Mill Stream by Hertford Lock; there may have been dredging recently undertaken and [...] thus remains a possible alternative context - the river itself.". Below this is recorded "Context, 8b. SINGLE FIND". In the bottom right corner of the card the following is recorded "RSO 17/7/80, Rec. [...] Aug 80, Source 8b. A., Sub. Inf. G. Davies - Hertford [...] 17/7/80.". This could possibly be the date of discovery, although since only two of the three dates match, with the third being a month later, I couldn't be sure. With the transcribing of the measurements, what was recorded as "max. B 5.8" I took to mean the thickness of the item. The information under the headings of "Typology", "Manufacture", "Condition" and "Attached Material" transcribed and placed in the description box, as this seemed the best fit.
description: Typology, flattened midnib only slightly convex bordered by strongly con[...]cave edge bevels, [...] symmetrical, flattish inside with sporadic facets [...] edges - no lipping or other indications that they are product of reworkings, Manufacture, midnib thinned in profile for hilt-plate, possible indications of its higher extension [...], flattening thus likely from post-[...] working, or re-working., Condition, edge little jagged, [...] sharp;, butt irregularities prob. original, no obvious breaks since manufacture., Attached Material, traces of [...] soil embedded, tending to chalky [...] in parts
